  "prompt": "What do you think the best English songs\uff1f?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" English songs is highly subjective and can vary widely depending on personal taste, cultural background, and musical preferences. However, several songs have achieved legendary status due to their widespread acclaim, cultural impact, and timeless appeal. Here\u2019s a list of some widely recognized and beloved English songs across various genres and eras:\n\n### Classic Rock & Pop:\n1. **The Beatles - \"Hey Jude\"** (1968)  \n   - A timeless anthem of hope and perseverance, often regarded as one of the greatest songs of all time.  \n2. **Queen - \"Bohemian Rhapsody\"** (1975)  \n   - A groundbreaking rock operetta blending genres and featuring Freddie Mercury's iconic vocals.  \n3. **Led Zeppelin - \"Stairway to Heaven\"** (1971)  \n   - A mystical and epic rock ballad that remains a cornerstone of classic rock.  \n\n### Soul & R&B:\n4. **Aretha Franklin - \"Respect\"** (1967)  \n   - A powerful anthem of empowerment and one of the most iconic songs in music history.  \n5. **Marvin Gaye - \"What's Going On\"** (1971)  \n   - A socially conscious masterpiece addressing war, poverty, and injustice.  \n\n### Pop & Contemporary:\n6. **Michael Jackson - \"Thriller\"** (1982)  \n   - A groundbreaking pop and dance hit with an iconic music video.  \n7. **Whitney Houston - \"I Will Always Love You\"** (1992)  \n   - A breathtaking ballad showcasing Houston's vocal prowess.  \n8. **Adele - \"Someone Like You\"** (2011)  \n   - A heartfelt ballad that resonated with millions worldwide.  \n\n### Hip-Hop & Rap:\n9. **Eminem - \"Lose Yourself\"** (2002)  \n   - An inspiring anthem that became the first rap song to win an Academy Award for Best Original Song.  \n10. **Tupac Shakur - \"Changes\"** (1998)  \n    - A poignant reflection on social issues and inequality.  \n\n### Modern Pop & Cross-Genre Hits:\n11. **Ed Sheeran - \"Shape of You\"** (2017)  \n    - A global chart-topper blending pop, dancehall, and R&B.  \n12. **Billie Eilish - \"Bad Guy\"** (2019)  \n    - A dark, minimalist pop hit that defined a new era of music.  \n\n### Timeless Ballads:\n13. **Elton John - \"Your Song\"** (1970)  \n    - A beautiful and heartfelt ode to love.  \n14. **John Lennon - \"Imagine\"** (1971)  \n    - A utopian anthem advocating peace and unity.  \n\n### Iconic Dance & Electronic:\n15. **Daft Punk - \"Get Lucky\"** (2013)  \n    - A funky, disco-inspired track that dominated the airwaves.  \n\nThe \"best\" songs ultimately depend on what resonates with you, whether it's the melody, lyrics, or emotional impact. These tracks, however, have left an indelible mark on music history and continue to inspire generations.",
